==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Helianthin
<hw>He`li*an"thin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. fr. L.
<ets>helianthes</ets>, or NL. <ets>helianthus</ets>, sunflower, in
allusion to its color.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An artificial,
orange dyestuff, analogous to tropaolin, and like it used as an
indicator in alkalimetry; -- called also <altname>methyl
orange</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Helianthoid</ent>⟦br⟧
